@startuml
' @id(DOM-CANVAS-VIEW)
' @desc(DOM-CANVAS-VIEW, "View state of the diagram canvas: base zoom and pan plus the center-fixed fisheye parameters (enabled, strength, radius) whose focal point is the canvas centre.")
' Objective-side domain: the canvas view state. The fisheye is a
' display-time transform parameterised here; its focal point is the
' canvas centre, not the cursor.
title Diagram canvas view state (objective)

class CanvasView {
  + baseZoom : float
  + pan : Vec2
  + fisheyeEnabled : bool
  + fisheyeStrength : float
  + fisheyeRadius : float
  + focal() : Vec2
}

note bottom of CanvasView
  baseZoom is driven only by scroll-at-cursor; pan only
  by drag. focal() returns the canvas-rect centre (the
  fisheye is center-fixed — see OCL-FISHEYE-FOCAL-CENTER).
  fisheyeStrength is bounded; 0 means the plain base
  placement (no warp). No toolbar zoom controls exist.
end note
@enduml
